{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:job.21",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 21,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 21",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 21 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.21.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:1",
      "text": "Then Job answered:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.21.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:2",
      "text": "“Listen carefully to my words, and let this be your consolation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.21.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:3",
      "text": "Bear with me, and I will speak, and after I have spoken, mock on.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.21.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:4",
      "text": "As for me, is my complaint against man? Why should I not be impatient?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.21.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:5",
      "text": "Look at me, and be appalled, and lay your hand upon your mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.21.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:6",
      "text": "When I think of it I am dismayed, and shuddering seizes my flesh.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.21.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:7",
      "text": "Why do the wicked live, reach old age, and grow mighty in power?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.21.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:8",
      "text": "Their children are established in their presence, and their offspring before their eyes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.21.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:9",
      "text": "Their houses are safe from fear, and no rod of God is upon them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.21.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:10",
      "text": "Their bull breeds without fail; their cow calves, and does not cast her calf.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.21.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:11",
      "text": "They send forth their little ones like a flock, and their children dance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.21.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:12",
      "text": "They sing to the tambourine and the lyre, and rejoice to the sound of the pipe.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.21.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:13",
      "text": "They spend their days in prosperity, and in peace they go down to Sheol.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.21.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:14",
      "text": "They say to God, ‘Depart from us! We do not desire the knowledge of thy ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.21.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:15",
      "text": "What is the Almighty, that we should serve him? And what profit do we get if we pray to him?’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.21.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:16",
      "text": "Behold, is not their prosperity in their hand? The counsel of the wicked is far from me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.21.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:17",
      "text": "“How often is it that the lamp of the wicked is put out? That their calamity comes upon them? That God distributes pains in his anger?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.21.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:18",
      "text": "That they are like straw before the wind, and like chaff that the storm carries away?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.21.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:19",
      "text": "You say, ‘God stores up their iniquity for their sons.’ Let him recompense it to themselves, that they may know it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.21.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:20",
      "text": "Let their own eyes see their destruction, and let them drink of the wrath of the Almighty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.21.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:21",
      "text": "For what do they care for their houses after them, when the number of their months is cut off?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.21.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:22",
      "text": "Will any teach God knowledge, seeing that he judges those that are on high?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.21.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:23",
      "text": "One dies in full prosperity, being wholly at ease and secure,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.21.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:24",
      "text": "his body full of fat and the marrow of his bones moist.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.21.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:25",
      "text": "Another dies in bitterness of soul, never having tasted of good.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.21.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:26",
      "text": "They lie down alike in the dust, and the worms cover them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.21.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:27",
      "text": "“Behold, I know your thoughts, and your schemes to wrong me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.21.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:28",
      "text": "For you say, ‘Where is the house of the prince? Where is the tent in which the wicked dwelt?’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.21.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:29",
      "text": "Have you not asked those who travel the roads, and do you not accept their testimony",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.21.30",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:30",
      "text": "that the wicked man is spared in the day of calamity, that he is rescued in the day of wrath?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.21.31",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:31",
      "text": "Who declares his way to his face, and who requites him for what he has done?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.21.32",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:32",
      "text": "When he is borne to the grave, watch is kept over his tomb.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.21.33",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:33",
      "text": "The clods of the valley are sweet to him; all men follow after him, and those who go before him are innumerable.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.21.34",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 21:34",
      "text": "How then will you comfort me with empty nothings? There is nothing left of your answers but falsehood.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
